==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Helleborin
<hw>Hel*leb"o*rin</hw> <pr>(? ⟦or⟧ ?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A poisonous glucoside found in several species
of hellebore, and extracted as a white crystalline substance with a
sharp tingling taste. It possesses the essential virtues of the plant;
-- called also <altname>elleborin</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Helleborism</ent>⟦br⟧
